":null},{"id":218286882,"node_id":"MDU6TGFiZWwyMTgyODY4ODI=","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/hashicorp/vagrant/labels/host/suse","name":"host/suse","color":"d4c5f9","default":false,"description":null}],"state":"closed","locked":true,"assignee":null,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":6,"created_at":"2019-06-23T16:15:12Z","updated_at":"2020-01-28T02:35:47Z","closed_at":"2019-06-25T18:00:56Z","author_association":"NONE","type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"> Please note that the Vagrant issue tracker is in priority reserved for bug reports ...\r\n\r\nNot a bug but I used the [documentation for fedora](https://www.vagrantup.com/docs/synced-folders/nfs.html) for my sudoers edit. Seems like is may work because SUSE also uses systemd for this and the binaries are in the places referenced there. \r\n```\r\nCmnd_Alias VAGRANT_EXPORTS_CHOWN = /bin/chown 0\\:0 /tmp/*\r\nCmnd_Alias VAGRANT_EXPORTS_MV = /bin/mv -f /tmp/* /etc/exports\r\nCmnd_Alias VAGRANT_NFSD_CHECK = /usr/bin/systemctl status --no-pager nfs-server.service\r\nCmnd_Alias VAGRANT_NFSD_START = /usr/bin/systemctl start nfs-server.service\r\nCmnd_Alias VAGRANT_NFSD_APPLY = /usr/sbin/exportfs -ar\r\n%vagrant ALL=(root) NOPASSWD: VAGRANT_EXPORTS_CHOWN, VAGRANT_EXPORTS_MV, VAGRANT_NFSD_CHECK, VAGRANT_NFSD_START, VAGRANT_NFSD_APPLY\r\n```\r\nI added my user to the vagrant group as it said and relogged into KDE but its not working, I still get asked for my sudo pw when doing a `vagrant up`\r\n\r\nIf I can get some help figuring this out you might then want to add a Open SUSE solution to the docs. Not sure what is different to fedora.","closed_by":{"login":"briancain","id":810277,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjgxMDI3Nw==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/810277?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/briancai